CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 27, 1959, pg. A1 reads: "Sees GOP Victory - Wilkinsburg Burgess Harry R. Rowland, above, told a a group of nominees, defeated candidates and party leaders last Friday, in Carlton House, that he was "confident that Republicans had the candidates and workers to win in November." Mr. Rowland will direct the GOP campaign. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: GOP campaign chairman Harry R. Rowland, speaking at GOP harmony meeting, standing in Carlton House with mirror and decorative wall sconce hung on marble wall
